<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-269] See if GraphVis (dot-2.26) can be made to work with mkdir1.gv</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-269</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The default build environment for the doc/protocol project was moved from RHEL6 to RHEL7 because the former included a version of GraphViz&apos;s &apos;dot&apos; program (dot-2.26) that segfaults. Since most users of this project will be free to use later working versions of &apos;dot&apos; this is not a serious issue, for now. It would be good to know why there is a problem and if there is a fix. Documenting the issue so that people aren&apos;t surprised is also good.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I do know know the version of &apos;dot&apos; on RHEL7 (the one that works) but the following have been shown to work:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ubuntu 12.04 dot-2.36&lt;br/&gt;
Mac 10.10.2 (Yosemite) ports installed dot-2.38.0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All of this may be very particular to the mkdir1.gv file, or it may have wider implications. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
